    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>所有引言来自 <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/quotes/search?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=sex&commit=Search" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Goodreads</a>。<br> 翻译：<a href="dearbojack.github.io"><em>PlayerUnknown</em></a></p><blockquote><p>“Everything in the world is about sex except sex. Sex is about power.” ― Oscar Wilde<br>世上万物皆与性有关，唯独性本身除外。性关乎权力。</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>“Man may have discovered fire, but women discovered how to play with it.” ― Candace Bushnell, Sex and the City<br>男人发现了火，女人发现了如何玩火。</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>“Fighting for peace is like screwing for virginity.” ― George Carlin<br>为了和平而斗争，就好比为了贞操去做爱。</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>“Writing is like sex. First you do it for love, then you do it for your friends, and then you do it for money.” ― Virginia Woolf<br>写作如同性爱。起先为了爱，然后为了朋友，然后为了钱。</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>“Sex is part of nature. I go along with nature.” ― Marilyn Monroe<br>性爱是本性的一部分，我选择追随本性。</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>“The difference between sex and love is that sex relieves tension and love causes it.” ― Woody Allen<br>性和爱之间的区别在于，性让人放松，爱让人紧张。</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>“I don’t know the question, but sex is definitely the answer.” ― Woody Allen<br>我不知道问题是什么，但答案肯定是性。</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>“It’s not true that I had nothing on. I had the radio on.” ― Marilyn Monroe<br>说我身无一物不太准确，我身上有电波。</p></blockquote>]]></content>
    
